HEADWORD: Gier-eagle
<hw>Gier"-ea`gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. D.
<ets>gier</ets> vulture, G. <ets>gier</ets>, and E.
<ets>gyrfalcon</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A bird referred to
in the Bible (<au>Lev. xi. 18</au>and <au>Deut. xiv. 17</au>) as
unclean, probably the Egyptian vulture (<spn>Neophron
percnopterus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

